ENTRY            31871   20260212   20260508   20260508       3222
SUBENT        31871001   20260212   20260508   20260508       3222
BIB                 13         39
TITLE      Measurement of spectrum averaged cross sections in
            LR-0 benchmark reference neutron field
AUTHOR     (M.Kostal, E.Losa, S.Simakov, T.Czakoj, M.Schulc,
            J.Simon, V.Rypar, M.Marecek, J.Uhlir, A.Krechlerova,
            T.Peltan, R.Posvar, Z.Matej, D.Bernard, A.Trkov,
            R.Capote)
INSTITUTE  (3CZRUJV,2GERKFK,2FR CAD,3SLNIJS,3ZZZIAE)
           (3CZRCZR) Masaryk University, Brno, Czech Republic
REFERENCE  (J,ANE,206,110616,2024)
FACILITY   (REAC,3CZRUJV) LR-0 reactor at the research centre Rez,
            using VVER-1000 type fuel. The special core features a
            dry hexagonal channel (apothem 11.7 cm) for sample
            irradiation.
INC-SOURCE (REAC)
INC-SPECT  LR-0 reactor spectrum
DETECTOR   (HPGE) Efficiency curve and coincidence summing
            factors determined using MCNP6
           (SCIN) The low-background Quantulus GCT 6220 liquid
            scintillation spectrometer was used exclusively to
            measure 14C activity.
METHOD     (ACTIV)
ADD-RES    The SACS averaged in LR-0 spectrum above 6 MeV were
            multiplied by a factor of 3.5942 to convert them into
            SACS averaged in 235U(nth,f) PFNS as listed in Table 9
CORRECTION corrected for:
           . decay correction
           . detector efficiency
           . coincidence summing effect
           . spectral shift
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) Uncertainty propagated from
           . radionuclide half-life values
           . branching ratios
           (ERR-S,,1.5) Counting statistics (<1.5%) are due to
           . gross peak area
           . Compton continuum area
           . background area
           . calibration uncertainty propagation
           (ERR-1) Detector efficiency (~1.9%)
HISTORY    (20260212C) VT
ENDBIB              39
COMMON               2          3
EN-DUMMY   ERR-1
MEV        PER-CENT
         1.        1.9
ENDCOMMON            3
